Latest Laravel Installation (Step-by-Step)

Laravel is installed using Composer, so Composer must already be installed.

🔷 1. Requirements (Very Important)

Before installing Laravel, ensure:

✔ PHP installed
PHP ≥ 8.1 (recommended 8.2+)
php -v

✔ Composer installed
composer -V

✔ Required PHP extensions enabled:
OpenSSL
PDO
Mbstring
Tokenizer
XML
Ctype
JSON
💻 2. Install Laravel (Latest Method)

There are 2 ways:

✅ METHOD 1 (Recommended): Using Composer create-project
🔷 Step 1: Open CMD / Terminal

Go to your project folder:

cd C:\xampp\htdocs

🔷 Step 2: Create Laravel Project
composer create-project laravel/laravel myapp


👉 This installs latest Laravel automatically.

🔷 Step 3: Move into project
cd myapp

🔷 Step 4: Run Laravel server
php artisan serve

🔷 Step 5: Open in browser
http://127.0.0.1:8000


✔ Laravel home page will appear

🚀 METHOD 2 (Modern Laravel Installer – Faster)
🔷 Step 1: Install Laravel Installer globally
composer global require laravel/installer

🔷 Step 2: Create project
laravel new myapp

🔷 Step 3: Run server
cd myapp
php artisan serve

🔷 3. Laravel Project Structure (Important)
myapp/
 ├── app/            → Business logic (Models, Controllers)
 ├── bootstrap/      → Framework startup
 ├── config/         → Configuration files
 ├── database/       → Migrations & seeders
 ├── public/         → Entry point (index.php)
 ├── resources/      → Views (Blade templates)
 ├── routes/         → URL routing
 ├── storage/        → Logs, cache
 ├── vendor/         → Composer dependencies

🔷 4. Important Laravel Commands
✔ Start server
php artisan serve

✔ Create controller
php artisan make:controller UserController

✔ Create model
php artisan make:model Product

✔ Run migrations
php artisan migrate

🔷 5. Latest Laravel Features (2025–2026)

✔ Improved performance (faster boot time)
✔ Better routing system
✔ Enhanced security patches
✔ Strong API support
✔ Better Eloquent ORM optimization
✔ Improved queue system
✔ Modern PHP 8.2+ support

🔷 6. Common Issues & Fixes
❌ “PHP not recognized”

✔ Add PHP path to Environment Variables

❌ Composer error

✔ Run:

composer install

❌ Port already in use

✔ Change port:

php artisan serve --port=8080

🔷 7. Real-World Usage

Laravel is used for:

E-commerce websites
Banking systems
APIs for mobile apps
Admin dashboards
SaaS platforms
